        <num>CC 1241</num>
        <heading>1241.  Collation by great grandchildren and more remote descendants</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1241.  Collation by great grandchildren and more remote descendants.
What has been said in the three preceding articles, of grandchildren inheriting from their grandfather or grandmother, must be understood of the great-grandchildren and other lawful descendants called to inherit from their ascendants, either in their own name or by right of representation.</p>
        </content>
